00:14:12.193 --> 00:14:15.922
Incoming livestream: a quick slide on intertrust authority before I go to the examples, right?


153
00:14:16.833 --> 00:14:20.413
Incoming livestream: I said Intel Trust Authority is that independent attestation system.


154
00:14:21.093 --> 00:14:25.583
Incoming livestream: Okay? It's available at a SaaS, it's available for on-prem deployments.


155
00:14:25.903 --> 00:14:31.392
Incoming livestream: And… Through one API, you can get attestation of your CPUs.


156
00:14:31.503 --> 00:14:40.372
Incoming livestream: and your GPUs as well. It could be one NVIDIA H100, one NVIDIA Blackwell, or it could be 8 Blackwells on the system.


157
00:14:41.103 --> 00:14:43.493
Incoming livestream: You get unified manifestation of all of that.


158
00:14:44.633 --> 00:15:01.532
Incoming livestream: Okay? And why is that important? As an application person, you don't want to deal with multiple workflows. I don't want to deal with a workflow for Intel CPUs. I don't want to deal for a workflow for NVIDIA GPUs. That's why we work together, the two companies, and we have this


159
00:15:01.783 --> 00:15:11.603
Incoming livestream: unified API, where you make one call, it figures out, hey, I am connected to two GPUs, so I need to make sure the attestation happens for both of those.


160
00:15:12.733 --> 00:15:24.952
Incoming livestream: Okay? Alright, so much for theory. Now, let me show you examples of this, okay? This is a release from Google called Google Confidential Space. How many of you heard of Confidential Space from Google?


161
00:15:26.103 --> 00:15:28.893
Incoming livestream: Maybe a few, okay. So very quickly…


162
00:15:29.193 --> 00:15:37.412
Incoming livestream: Google Confidential Space is like a data clean room for AI, okay? What it is, is you can take your containers.


163
00:15:38.163 --> 00:15:44.593
Incoming livestream: You run it in a confidential computing environment, the…


164
00:15:44.943 --> 00:15:47.783
Incoming livestream: OS that runs inside that VM,


165
00:15:48.183 --> 00:15:53.672
Incoming livestream: Your application, which is your container, Everything is measured


166
00:15:53.873 --> 00:15:57.163
Incoming livestream: And that measurements are available for verification.


167
00:15:58.503 --> 00:16:04.012
Incoming livestream: And the confidential space environment, as part of launching your container.


168
00:16:04.413 --> 00:16:07.112
Incoming livestream: will attest to Intel Trust Authority.


169
00:16:07.653 --> 00:16:16.272
Incoming livestream: And the trust authority verifies all the policies that need to be verified, and it's gonna give a token, which is called an attestation token.


170
00:16:17.063 --> 00:16:22.573
Incoming livestream: This token is now given to all the data sources.


171
00:16:23.113 --> 00:16:26.463
Incoming livestream: Whether it is a data source in Google Cloud.


172
00:16:26.573 --> 00:16:31.392
Incoming livestream: whether it's a data source in Amazon, or whether it's on-prem for you.


